qas.question: Who operated as the "police of Europe"?
In what year did the Hungarian Revolution take place?
Who did Russia help during the Hungarian Revolution?
In exchange for helping Austria, Russia wanted to be freely able to handle any issues they had with who?

context: <a0_0>Russia<a0_0/>, as a member of the Holy Alliance, had operated as the "police of Europe", maintaining the balance of power that had been established in the <a1_0>Treaty of Vienna<a1_0/> in 1815. Russia had assisted <a3_0>Austria<a3_0/>'s efforts in suppressing the Hungarian Revolution of <a2_0>1848<a2_0/>, and expected gratitude; it wanted a free hand in settling its problems with the <a4_0>Ottoman Empire<a4_0/> — the "sick man of Europe". The United Kingdom could not tolerate Russian dominance of Ottoman affairs, as that would challenge the British domination of the eastern Mediterranean.
